# Bullion Tracker Mobile - Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in values for your environment
#
# NOTE: For Expo projects, environment variables are read via app.json "extra" config.
# Update app.json extra.apiUrl for your environment instead of using .env directly.
# This file documents the required configuration values.

# =============================================================================
# API Configuration
# =============================================================================

# Backend API URL - REQUIRED for app to function
# Update in app.json > expo > extra > apiUrl
#
# Development (iOS Simulator): http://localhost:3001
# Development (Android Emulator): http://10.0.2.2:3001
# Development (Physical Device): http://YOUR_COMPUTER_IP:3001
#   - Find your IP: ipconfig getifaddr en0 (macOS) or ipconfig (Windows)
#   - Example: http://192.168.1.100:3001
# Production: https://your-production-url.com
#
# Currently configured in app.json:
# API_URL=http://localhost:3001

# =============================================================================
# Optional: Metal Price API
# =============================================================================
# Get your free API key at: https://metalpriceapi.com
# Note: Mobile app typically fetches prices through the backend API
# This is only needed if fetching prices directly from mobile
#
# Currently configured in app.json:
# METAL_PRICE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# Development Tips
# =============================================================================
#
# iOS Simulator:
#   - Uses localhost directly (no IP needed)
#   - Set apiUrl to "http://localhost:3001"
#
# Android Emulator:
#   - Cannot reach localhost directly
#   - Set apiUrl to "http://10.0.2.2:3001"
#
# Physical Device (same WiFi network):
#   - Must use your computer's local IP address
#   - Run: ipconfig getifaddr en0 (macOS) to find IP
#   - Set apiUrl to "http://YOUR_IP:3001"
#   - Ensure firewall allows port 3001
#
# Production Build:
#   - Set apiUrl to your production API URL
#   - Update before running: npx expo build:ios or npx expo build:android
#
# =============================================================================
# PRODUCTION SECURITY REQUIREMENTS
# =============================================================================
#
# CRITICAL: For production deployment, the API URL MUST use HTTPS:
#   - apiUrl: "https://your-production-domain.com"
#   - Never use HTTP in production (credentials transmitted in plain text)
#   - Ensure SSL certificate is valid and not expired
#
# Security checklist:
# [ ] API URL uses HTTPS (not HTTP)
# [ ] API URL points to production server (not localhost or local IP)
# [ ] No test credentials in source code (verified Phase 13)
# [ ] Token storage uses SecureStore (already implemented)
#
# Last security review: 2026-01-10 (Phase 13: Credential Cleanup)
